lead_paragraph: The political news cycle is fast, and keeping up can be overwhelming. Trying to find differing perspectives worth your time is even harder. That’s why we have scoured the internet for political writing from the right and left that you might not have seen.

snippet: In recent weeks, the team has begun reaching out to potential buyers in the United States and Asia, according to people briefed on the discussions.
lead_paragraph: The owners of D.C. United, Washington’s Major League Soccer team, are quietly weighing a sale of the franchise, people briefed on the discussions said on Sunday.

abstract: The absence of strong challengers to Mayor Bill de Blasio and other citywide candidates is reflected in the absence of independent spending.
snippet: The absence of strong challengers to Mayor Bill de Blasio and other citywide candidates is reflected in the absence of independent spending.
lead_paragraph: Seven months ago, Mayor Bill de Blasio’s campaign had an ominous warning for supporters: Powerful forces had already spent $13 million “against us” in the election and were planning to pour more money into the race to ensure the mayor did not get a second term.

abstract: The City Council on Thursday took a step toward the long-awaited rezoning of East Midtown, with even taller office towers in store for the business hub.
snippet: The City Council on Thursday took a step toward the long-awaited rezoning of East Midtown, with even taller office towers in store for the business hub.
lead_paragraph: The Roman Catholic Archdiocese of New York may know something about divine intervention. But to get to Mayor Bill de Blasio on a real estate negotiation potentially worth hundreds of millions of dollars, it hired lobbyists.

abstract: Looking on the bright side of a plan to take out some seats from subway cars, standing would most likely let commuters eat an extra Life Saver a day.
snippet: Looking on the bright side of a plan to take out some seats from subway cars, standing would most likely let commuters eat an extra Life Saver a day.
lead_paragraph: In relentless pursuit of silver linings, we bring you research on the benefits of standing vs. sitting, as transit officials prepare to remove seats from some subway cars on the L line and the 42nd Street shuttle.

abstract: Read about how the other side thinks: Writers across the political spectrum on the president’s barring of transgender people from military service.

lead_paragraph: The political news cycle is fast, and keeping up can be overwhelming. Trying to find differing perspectives worth your time is even harder. That’s why we have scoured the internet for political writing from the right and left that you might not have seen.
